41// This function assumes that all of the fields are either of default value or are
42// present in the raw data.
43NetCommandRef * NetPacket::ConstructNetCommandMsgFromRawData(UnsignedByte *data, UnsignedShort dataLength) {
44 NetCommandType commandType = NETCOMMANDTYPE_GAMECOMMAND;
45 UnsignedShort commandID = 0;
46 UnsignedInt frame = 0;
47 UnsignedByte playerID = 0;
48 UnsignedByte relay = 0;
49
50 Int offset = 0;
51 Bool notDone = TRUE;
52 NetCommandRef *ref = NULL;
53 NetCommandMsg *msg = NULL;
54
55 while ((offset < (Int)dataLength) && notDone) {
56 if (data[offset] == 'T') {
57 ++offset;
58 memcpy(&commandType, data + offset, sizeof(UnsignedByte));
59 offset += sizeof(UnsignedByte);
60 } else if (data[offset] == 'R') {
61 ++offset;
62 memcpy(&relay, data + offset, sizeof(UnsignedByte));
63 offset += sizeof(UnsignedByte);
64 } else if (data[offset] == 'P') {
65 ++offset;
66 memcpy(&playerID, data + offset, sizeof(UnsignedByte));
67 offset += sizeof(UnsignedByte);
68 } else if (data[offset] == 'C') {
69 ++offset;
70 memcpy(&commandID, data + offset, sizeof(UnsignedShort));
71 offset += sizeof(UnsignedShort);
72 } else if (data[offset] == 'F') {
73 ++offset;
74 memcpy(&frame, data + offset, sizeof(UnsignedInt));
75 offset += sizeof(UnsignedInt);
76 } else if (data[offset] == 'D') {
77 ++offset;
78 if (commandType == NETCOMMANDTYPE_GAMECOMMAND) {
79 msg = readGameMessage(data, offset);
80 } else if (commandType == NETCOMMANDTYPE_ACKBOTH) {
81 msg = readAckBothMessage(data, offset);
82 } else if (commandType == NETCOMMANDTYPE_ACKSTAGE1) {
83 msg = readAckStage1Message(data, offset);
84 } else if (commandType == NETCOMMANDTYPE_ACKSTAGE2) {
85 msg = readAckStage2Message(data, offset);
86 } else if (commandType == NETCOMMANDTYPE_FRAMEINFO) {
87 msg = readFrameMessage(data, offset);
88 } else if (commandType == NETCOMMANDTYPE_PLAYERLEAVE) {
89 msg = readPlayerLeaveMessage(data, offset);
90 } else if (commandType == NETCOMMANDTYPE_RUNAHEADMETRICS) {
91 msg = readRunAheadMetricsMessage(data, offset);
92 } else if (commandType == NETCOMMANDTYPE_RUNAHEAD) {
93 msg = readRunAheadMessage(data, offset);
94 } else if (commandType == NETCOMMANDTYPE_DESTROYPLAYER) {
95 msg = readDestroyPlayerMessage(data, offset);
96 } else if (commandType == NETCOMMANDTYPE_KEEPALIVE) {
97 msg = readKeepAliveMessage(data, offset);
98 } else if (commandType == NETCOMMANDTYPE_DISCONNECTKEEPALIVE) {
99 msg = readDisconnectKeepAliveMessage(data, offset);
100 } else if (commandType == NETCOMMANDTYPE_DISCONNECTPLAYER) {
101 msg = readDisconnectPlayerMessage(data, offset);
102 } else if (commandType == NETCOMMANDTYPE_PACKETROUTERQUERY) {
103 msg = readPacketRouterQueryMessage(data, offset);
104 } else if (commandType == NETCOMMANDTYPE_PACKETROUTERACK) {
105 msg = readPacketRouterAckMessage(data, offset);
106 } else if (commandType == NETCOMMANDTYPE_DISCONNECTCHAT) {
107 msg = readDisconnectChatMessage(data, offset);
108 } else if (commandType == NETCOMMANDTYPE_DISCONNECTVOTE) {
109 msg = readDisconnectVoteMessage(data, offset);
110 } else if (commandType == NETCOMMANDTYPE_CHAT) {
111 msg = readChatMessage(data, offset);
112 } else if (commandType == NETCOMMANDTYPE_PROGRESS) {
113 msg = readProgressMessage(data, offset);
114 } else if (commandType == NETCOMMANDTYPE_LOADCOMPLETE) {
115 msg = readLoadCompleteMessage(data, offset);
116 } else if (commandType == NETCOMMANDTYPE_TIMEOUTSTART) {
117 msg = readTimeOutGameStartMessage(data, offset);
118 } else if (commandType == NETCOMMANDTYPE_WRAPPER) {
119 msg = readWrapperMessage(data, offset);
120 } else if (commandType == NETCOMMANDTYPE_FILE) {
121 msg = readFileMessage(data, offset);
122 } else if (commandType == NETCOMMANDTYPE_FILEANNOUNCE) {
123 msg = readFileAnnounceMessage(data, offset);
124 } else if (commandType == NETCOMMANDTYPE_FILEPROGRESS) {
125 msg = readFileProgressMessage(data, offset);
126 } else if (commandType == NETCOMMANDTYPE_DISCONNECTFRAME) {
127 msg = readDisconnectFrameMessage(data, offset);
128 } else if (commandType == NETCOMMANDTYPE_DISCONNECTSCREENOFF) {
129 msg = readDisconnectScreenOffMessage(data, offset);
130 } else if (commandType == NETCOMMANDTYPE_FRAMERESENDREQUEST) {
131 msg = readFrameResendRequestMessage(data, offset);
132 }
133
134 msg->setExecutionFrame(frame);
135 msg->setID(commandID);
136 msg->setPlayerID(playerID);
137 msg->setNetCommandType(commandType);
138
139 ref = NEW_NETCOMMANDREF(msg);
140
141 ref->setRelay(relay);
142
143 msg->detach();
144 msg = NULL;
145
146 notDone = FALSE;
147 }
148 }
149
150 return ref;
151}

153NetPacketList NetPacket::ConstructBigCommandPacketList(NetCommandRef *ref) {
154 // if we don't have a unique command ID, then the wrapped command cannot
155 // be identified. Therefore don't allow commands without a unique ID to
156 // be wrapped.
157 NetCommandMsg *msg = ref->getCommand();
158
159 if (!DoesCommandRequireACommandID(msg->getNetCommandType())) {
160 DEBUG_CRASH(("Trying to wrap a command that doesn't have a unique command ID"));
161 return NULL;
162 }
163
164 UnsignedInt bufferSize = GetBufferSizeNeededForCommand(msg); // need to implement. I have a drinking problem.
165 UnsignedByte *bigPacketData = NULL;
166
167 NetPacketList packetList;
168
169 // create the buffer for the huge message and fill the buffer with that message.
170 UnsignedInt bigPacketCurrentOffset = 0;
171 bigPacketData = NEW UnsignedByte[bufferSize];
172 FillBufferWithCommand(bigPacketData, ref);
173
174 // create the wrapper command message we'll be using.
175 NetWrapperCommandMsg *wrapperMsg = newInstance(NetWrapperCommandMsg);
176 // get the amount of space needed for the wrapper message, not including the wrapped command data.
177 UnsignedInt wrapperSize = GetBufferSizeNeededForCommand(wrapperMsg);
178 UnsignedInt commandSizePerPacket = MAX_PACKET_SIZE - wrapperSize;
179
180 UnsignedInt numChunks = bufferSize / commandSizePerPacket;
181 if ((bufferSize % commandSizePerPacket) > 0) {
182 ++numChunks;
183 }
184 UnsignedInt currentChunk = 0;
185
186 // create the packets and the wrapper messages.
187 while (currentChunk < numChunks) {
188 NetPacket *packet = newInstance(NetPacket);
189
190 UnsignedShort dataSizeThisPacket = commandSizePerPacket;
191 if ((bufferSize - bigPacketCurrentOffset) < dataSizeThisPacket) {
192 dataSizeThisPacket = bufferSize - bigPacketCurrentOffset;
193 }
194
195 if (DoesCommandRequireACommandID(wrapperMsg->getNetCommandType())) {
196 wrapperMsg->setID(GenerateNextCommandID());
197 }
198 wrapperMsg->setPlayerID(msg->getPlayerID());
199 wrapperMsg->setExecutionFrame(msg->getExecutionFrame());
200
201 wrapperMsg->setChunkNumber(currentChunk);
202 wrapperMsg->setNumChunks(numChunks);
203 wrapperMsg->setDataOffset(bigPacketCurrentOffset);
204 wrapperMsg->setData(bigPacketData + bigPacketCurrentOffset, dataSizeThisPacket);
205 wrapperMsg->setTotalDataLength(bufferSize);
206 wrapperMsg->setWrappedCommandID(msg->getID());
207
208 bigPacketCurrentOffset += dataSizeThisPacket;
209
210 NetCommandRef * ref = NEW_NETCOMMANDREF(wrapperMsg);
211 ref->setRelay(ref->getRelay());
212
213 if (packet->addCommand(ref) == FALSE) {
214 DEBUG_LOG(("NetPacket::BeginBigCommandPacketList - failed to add a wrapper command to the packet\n")); // I still have a drinking problem.
215 }
216
217 packetList.push_back(packet);
218
219 ref->deleteInstance();
220 ref = NULL;
221
222 ++currentChunk;
223 }
224 wrapperMsg->detach();
225 wrapperMsg = NULL;
226
227 delete bigPacketData;
228 bigPacketData = NULL;
229
230 return packetList;
231}

233UnsignedInt NetPacket::GetBufferSizeNeededForCommand(NetCommandMsg *msg) {
234 // This is where the fun begins...
235
236 if (msg == NULL) {
237 return TRUE; // There was nothing to add, so it was successful.
238 }
239
240 switch(msg->getNetCommandType())
241 {
242 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_GAMECOMMAND:
243 return GetGameCommandSize(msg);
244 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_ACKSTAGE1:
245 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_ACKSTAGE2:
246 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_ACKBOTH:
247 return GetAckCommandSize(msg);
248 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_FRAMEINFO:
249 return GetFrameCommandSize(msg);
250 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_PLAYERLEAVE:
251 return GetPlayerLeaveCommandSize(msg);
252 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_RUNAHEADMETRICS:
253 return GetRunAheadMetricsCommandSize(msg);
254 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_RUNAHEAD:
255 return GetRunAheadCommandSize(msg);
256 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_DESTROYPLAYER:
257 return GetDestroyPlayerCommandSize(msg);
258 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_KEEPALIVE:
259 return GetKeepAliveCommandSize(msg);
260 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_DISCONNECTKEEPALIVE:
261 return GetDisconnectKeepAliveCommandSize(msg);
262 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_DISCONNECTPLAYER:
263 return GetDisconnectPlayerCommandSize(msg);
264 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_PACKETROUTERQUERY:
265 return GetPacketRouterQueryCommandSize(msg);
266 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_PACKETROUTERACK:
267 return GetPacketRouterAckCommandSize(msg);
268 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_DISCONNECTCHAT:
269 return GetDisconnectChatCommandSize(msg);
270 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_DISCONNECTVOTE:
271 return GetDisconnectVoteCommandSize(msg);
272 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_CHAT:
273 return GetChatCommandSize(msg);
274 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_PROGRESS:
275 return GetProgressMessageSize(msg);
276 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_LOADCOMPLETE:
277 return GetLoadCompleteMessageSize(msg);
278 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_TIMEOUTSTART:
279 return GetTimeOutGameStartMessageSize(msg);
280 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_WRAPPER:
281 return GetWrapperCommandSize(msg);
282 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_FILE:
283 return GetFileCommandSize(msg);
284 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_FILEANNOUNCE:
285 return GetFileAnnounceCommandSize(msg);
286 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_FILEPROGRESS:
287 return GetFileProgressCommandSize(msg);
288 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_DISCONNECTFRAME:
289 return GetDisconnectFrameCommandSize(msg);
290 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_DISCONNECTSCREENOFF:
291 return GetDisconnectScreenOffCommandSize(msg);
292 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_FRAMERESENDREQUEST:
293 return GetFrameResendRequestCommandSize(msg);
294 default:
295 DEBUG_CRASH(("Unknown NETCOMMANDTYPE %d", msg->getNetCommandType()));
296 break;
297 }
298
299 return 0;
300}

302UnsignedInt NetPacket::GetGameCommandSize(NetCommandMsg *msg) {
303 NetGameCommandMsg *cmdMsg = (NetGameCommandMsg *)msg;
304
305 UnsignedShort msglen = 0;
306 msglen += sizeof(UnsignedInt) + sizeof(UnsignedByte); // frame number
307 msglen += sizeof(UnsignedByte) + sizeof(UnsignedByte); // player ID
308 msglen += sizeof(UnsignedByte) + sizeof(UnsignedByte); // relay
309 msglen += sizeof(UnsignedByte) + sizeof(UnsignedByte); // command type
310 msglen += sizeof(UnsignedShort) + sizeof(UnsignedByte); // command ID
311 msglen += sizeof(UnsignedByte); // the 'D' for the data section.
312
313 GameMessage *gmsg = cmdMsg->constructGameMessage();
314 GameMessageParser *parser = newInstance(GameMessageParser)(gmsg);
315
316 msglen += sizeof(GameMessage::Type);
317 msglen += sizeof(UnsignedByte);
318// Int numTypes = parser->getNumTypes();
319 GameMessageParserArgumentType *arg = parser->getFirstArgumentType();
320 while (arg != NULL) {
321 msglen += 2 * sizeof(UnsignedByte); // for the type and number of args of that type declaration.
322 GameMessageArgumentDataType type = arg->getType();
323 if (type == ARGUMENTDATATYPE_INTEGER) {
324 msglen += arg->getArgCount() * sizeof(Int);
325 } else if (type == ARGUMENTDATATYPE_REAL) {
326 msglen += arg->getArgCount() * sizeof(Real);
327 } else if (type == ARGUMENTDATATYPE_BOOLEAN) {
328 msglen += arg->getArgCount() * sizeof(Bool);
329 } else if (type == ARGUMENTDATATYPE_OBJECTID) {
330 msglen += arg->getArgCount() * sizeof(ObjectID);
331 } else if (type == ARGUMENTDATATYPE_DRAWABLEID) {
332 msglen += arg->getArgCount() * sizeof(DrawableID);
333 } else if (type == ARGUMENTDATATYPE_TEAMID) {
334 msglen += arg->getArgCount() * sizeof(UnsignedInt);
335 } else if (type == ARGUMENTDATATYPE_LOCATION) {
336 msglen += arg->getArgCount() * sizeof(Coord3D);
337 } else if (type == ARGUMENTDATATYPE_PIXEL) {
338 msglen += arg->getArgCount() * sizeof(ICoord2D);
339 } else if (type == ARGUMENTDATATYPE_PIXELREGION) {
340 msglen += arg->getArgCount() * sizeof(IRegion2D);
341 } else if (type == ARGUMENTDATATYPE_TIMESTAMP) {
342 msglen += arg->getArgCount() * sizeof(UnsignedInt);
343 } else if (type == ARGUMENTDATATYPE_WIDECHAR) {
344 msglen += arg->getArgCount() * sizeof(WideChar);
345 }
346 arg = arg->getNext();
347 }
348
349 parser->deleteInstance();
350 parser = NULL;
351
352 gmsg->deleteInstance();
353 gmsg = NULL;
354
355 return msglen;
356}

650UnsignedInt NetPacket::GetFileCommandSize(NetCommandMsg *msg) {
651 NetFileCommandMsg *filemsg = (NetFileCommandMsg *)msg;
652 UnsignedInt msglen = 0;
653 msglen += sizeof(UnsignedByte) + sizeof(UnsignedByte); // 'T' and command type
654 msglen += sizeof(UnsignedByte) + sizeof(UnsignedByte); // 'P' and player ID
655 msglen += sizeof(UnsignedByte) + sizeof(UnsignedShort); // 'C' and command ID
656 msglen += sizeof(UnsignedByte) + sizeof(UnsignedByte); // 'R' and relay
657
658 ++msglen; // 'D'
659
660 msglen += filemsg->getPortableFilename().getLength() + 1; // PORTABLE filename and the terminating 0
661 msglen += sizeof(UnsignedInt); // file data length
662 msglen += filemsg->getFileLength(); // the file data
663
664 return msglen;

667UnsignedInt NetPacket::GetFileAnnounceCommandSize(NetCommandMsg *msg) {
668 NetFileAnnounceCommandMsg *filemsg = (NetFileAnnounceCommandMsg *)msg;
669 UnsignedInt msglen = 0;
670 msglen += sizeof(UnsignedByte) + sizeof(UnsignedByte); // 'T' and command type
671 msglen += sizeof(UnsignedByte) + sizeof(UnsignedByte); // 'P' and player ID
672 msglen += sizeof(UnsignedByte) + sizeof(UnsignedShort); // 'C' and command ID
673 msglen += sizeof(UnsignedByte) + sizeof(UnsignedByte); // 'R' and relay
674
675 ++msglen; // 'D'
676
677 msglen += filemsg->getPortableFilename().getLength() + 1; // PORTABLE filename and the terminating 0
678 msglen += sizeof(UnsignedShort); // m_fileID
679 msglen += sizeof(UnsignedByte); // m_playerMask
680
681 return msglen;
682}

738// this function assumes that buffer is already the correct size.
739void NetPacket::FillBufferWithCommand(UnsignedByte *buffer, NetCommandRef *ref) {
740 NetCommandMsg *msg = ref->getCommand();
741
742 switch(msg->getNetCommandType())
743 {
744 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_GAMECOMMAND:
745 FillBufferWithGameCommand(buffer, ref);
746 break;
747 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_ACKSTAGE1:
748 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_ACKSTAGE2:
749 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_ACKBOTH:
750 FillBufferWithAckCommand(buffer, ref);
751 break;
752 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_FRAMEINFO:
753 FillBufferWithFrameCommand(buffer, ref);
754 break;
755 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_PLAYERLEAVE:
756 FillBufferWithPlayerLeaveCommand(buffer, ref);
757 break;
758 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_RUNAHEADMETRICS:
759 FillBufferWithRunAheadMetricsCommand(buffer, ref);
760 break;
761 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_RUNAHEAD:
762 FillBufferWithRunAheadCommand(buffer, ref);
763 break;
764 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_DESTROYPLAYER:
765 FillBufferWithDestroyPlayerCommand(buffer, ref);
766 break;
767 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_KEEPALIVE:
768 FillBufferWithKeepAliveCommand(buffer, ref);
769 break;
770 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_DISCONNECTKEEPALIVE:
771 FillBufferWithDisconnectKeepAliveCommand(buffer, ref);
772 break;
773 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_DISCONNECTPLAYER:
774 FillBufferWithDisconnectPlayerCommand(buffer, ref);
775 break;
776 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_PACKETROUTERQUERY:
777 FillBufferWithPacketRouterQueryCommand(buffer, ref);
778 break;
779 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_PACKETROUTERACK:
780 FillBufferWithPacketRouterAckCommand(buffer, ref);
781 break;
782 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_DISCONNECTCHAT:
783 FillBufferWithDisconnectChatCommand(buffer, ref);
784 break;
785 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_DISCONNECTVOTE:
786 FillBufferWithDisconnectVoteCommand(buffer, ref);
787 break;
788 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_CHAT:
789 FillBufferWithChatCommand(buffer, ref);
790 break;
791 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_PROGRESS:
792 FillBufferWithProgressMessage(buffer, ref);
793 break;
794 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_LOADCOMPLETE:
795 FillBufferWithLoadCompleteMessage(buffer, ref);
796 break;
797 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_TIMEOUTSTART:
798 FillBufferWithTimeOutGameStartMessage(buffer, ref);
799 break;
800 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_FILE:
801 FillBufferWithFileMessage(buffer, ref);
802 break;
803 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_FILEANNOUNCE:
804 FillBufferWithFileAnnounceMessage(buffer, ref);
805 break;
806 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_FILEPROGRESS:
807 FillBufferWithFileProgressMessage(buffer, ref);
808 break;
809 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_DISCONNECTFRAME:
810 FillBufferWithDisconnectFrameMessage(buffer, ref);
811 break;
812 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_DISCONNECTSCREENOFF:
813 FillBufferWithDisconnectScreenOffMessage(buffer, ref);
814 break;
815 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_FRAMERESENDREQUEST:
816 FillBufferWithFrameResendRequestMessage(buffer, ref);
817 break;
818 default:
819 DEBUG_CRASH(("Unknown NETCOMMANDTYPE %d", msg->getNetCommandType()));
820 break;
821 }
822}

824void NetPacket::FillBufferWithGameCommand(UnsignedByte *buffer, NetCommandRef *msg) {
825 NetGameCommandMsg *cmdMsg = (NetGameCommandMsg *)(msg->getCommand());
826 UnsignedShort offset = 0;
827 // get the game message from the NetCommandMsg
828 GameMessage *gmsg = cmdMsg->constructGameMessage();
829
830 //DEBUG_LOG(("NetPacket::FillBufferWithGameCommand for command ID %d\n", cmdMsg->getID()));
831
832 // If necessary, put the NetCommandType into the packet.
833 buffer[offset] = 'T';
834 ++offset;
835 buffer[offset] = cmdMsg->getNetCommandType();
836 offset += sizeof(UnsignedByte);
837
838 // If necessary, put the execution frame into the packet.
839 buffer[offset] = 'F';
840 ++offset;
841 UnsignedInt newframe = cmdMsg->getExecutionFrame();
842 memcpy(buffer+offset, &newframe, sizeof(UnsignedInt));
843 offset += sizeof(UnsignedInt);
844
845 // If necessary, put the relay into the packet.
846 buffer[offset] = 'R';
847 ++offset;
848 UnsignedByte newRelay = msg->getRelay();
849 memcpy(buffer+offset, &newRelay, sizeof(UnsignedByte));
850 offset += sizeof(UnsignedByte);
851
852 // If necessary, put the playerID into the packet.
853 buffer[offset] = 'P';
854 ++offset;
855 buffer[offset] = cmdMsg->getPlayerID();
856 offset += sizeof(UnsignedByte);
857
858 // If necessary, specify the command ID of this command.
859 buffer[offset] = 'C';
860 ++offset;
861 UnsignedShort newID = cmdMsg->getID();
862 memcpy(buffer + offset, &newID, sizeof(UnsignedShort));
863 offset += sizeof(UnsignedShort);
864
865 buffer[offset] = 'D';
866 ++offset;
867
868 // Now copy the GameMessage type into the packet.
869 GameMessage::Type newType = gmsg->getType();
870 memcpy(buffer + offset, &newType, sizeof(GameMessage::Type));
871 offset += sizeof(GameMessage::Type);
872
873
874 GameMessageParser *parser = newInstance(GameMessageParser)(gmsg);
875 UnsignedByte numTypes = parser->getNumTypes();
876 memcpy(buffer + offset, &numTypes, sizeof(numTypes));
877 offset += sizeof(numTypes);
878
879 GameMessageParserArgumentType *argType = parser->getFirstArgumentType();
880 while (argType != NULL) {
881 UnsignedByte type = (UnsignedByte)(argType->getType());
882 memcpy(buffer + offset, &type, sizeof(type));
883 offset += sizeof(type);
884
885 UnsignedByte argTypeCount = argType->getArgCount();
886 memcpy(buffer + offset, &argTypeCount, sizeof(argTypeCount));
887 offset += sizeof(argTypeCount);
888
889 argType = argType->getNext();
890 }
891
892 Int numArgs = gmsg->getArgumentCount();
893 for (Int i = 0; i < numArgs; ++i) {
894 GameMessageArgumentDataType type = gmsg->getArgumentDataType(i);
895 GameMessageArgumentType arg = *(gmsg->getArgument(i));
896// writeGameMessageArgumentToPacket(type, arg);
897
898 if (type == ARGUMENTDATATYPE_INTEGER) {
899 memcpy(buffer + offset, &(arg.integer), sizeof(arg.integer));
900 offset += sizeof(arg.integer);
901 } else if (type == ARGUMENTDATATYPE_REAL) {
902 memcpy(buffer + offset, &(arg.real), sizeof(arg.real));
903 offset += sizeof(arg.real);
904 } else if (type == ARGUMENTDATATYPE_BOOLEAN) {
905 memcpy(buffer + offset, &(arg.boolean), sizeof(arg.boolean));
906 offset += sizeof(arg.boolean);
907 } else if (type == ARGUMENTDATATYPE_OBJECTID) {
908 memcpy(buffer + offset, &(arg.objectID), sizeof(arg.objectID));
909 offset += sizeof(arg.objectID);
910 } else if (type == ARGUMENTDATATYPE_DRAWABLEID) {
911 memcpy(buffer + offset, &(arg.drawableID), sizeof(arg.drawableID));
912 offset += sizeof(arg.drawableID);
913 } else if (type == ARGUMENTDATATYPE_TEAMID) {
914 memcpy(buffer + offset, &(arg.teamID), sizeof(arg.teamID));
915 offset += sizeof(arg.teamID);
916 } else if (type == ARGUMENTDATATYPE_LOCATION) {
917 memcpy(buffer + offset, &(arg.location), sizeof(arg.location));
918 offset += sizeof(arg.location);
919 } else if (type == ARGUMENTDATATYPE_PIXEL) {
920 memcpy(buffer + offset, &(arg.pixel), sizeof(arg.pixel));
921 offset += sizeof(arg.pixel);
922 } else if (type == ARGUMENTDATATYPE_PIXELREGION) {
923 memcpy(buffer + offset, &(arg.pixelRegion), sizeof(arg.pixelRegion));
924 offset += sizeof(arg.pixelRegion);
925 } else if (type == ARGUMENTDATATYPE_TIMESTAMP) {
926 memcpy(buffer + offset, &(arg.timestamp), sizeof(arg.timestamp));
927 offset += sizeof(arg.timestamp);
928 } else if (type == ARGUMENTDATATYPE_WIDECHAR) {
929 memcpy(buffer + offset, &(arg.wChar), sizeof(arg.wChar));
930 offset += sizeof(arg.wChar);
931 }
932 }
933
934 parser->deleteInstance();
935 parser = NULL;
936
937// DEBUG_LOG(("NetPacket::addGameMessage - added game message, frame %d, player %d, command ID %d\n", m_lastFrame, m_lastPlayerID, m_lastCommandID));
938
939 if (gmsg)
940 gmsg->deleteInstance();
941 gmsg = NULL;
942}

944void NetPacket::FillBufferWithAckCommand(UnsignedByte *buffer, NetCommandRef *msg) {
945// DEBUG_LOG(("NetPacket::FillBufferWithAckCommand - adding ack for command %d for player %d\n", cmdMsg->getCommandID(), msg->getCommand()->getPlayerID()));
946
947 NetCommandMsg *cmdMsg = msg->getCommand();
948 UnsignedShort offset = 0;
949
950 UnsignedShort commandID = 0;
951 UnsignedByte originalPlayerID = 0;
952
953 if (cmdMsg->getNetCommandType() == NETCOMMANDTYPE_ACKBOTH) {
954 NetAckBothCommandMsg *ackmsg = (NetAckBothCommandMsg *)msg;
955 commandID = ackmsg->getCommandID();
956 originalPlayerID = ackmsg->getOriginalPlayerID();
957 } else if (cmdMsg->getNetCommandType() == NETCOMMANDTYPE_ACKSTAGE1) {
958 NetAckStage1CommandMsg *ackmsg = (NetAckStage1CommandMsg *)msg;
959 commandID = ackmsg->getCommandID();
960 originalPlayerID = ackmsg->getOriginalPlayerID();
961 } else if (cmdMsg->getNetCommandType() == NETCOMMANDTYPE_ACKSTAGE2) {
962 NetAckStage2CommandMsg *ackmsg = (NetAckStage2CommandMsg *)msg;
963 commandID = ackmsg->getCommandID();
964 originalPlayerID = ackmsg->getOriginalPlayerID();
965 }
966
967 buffer[offset] = 'T';
968 ++offset;
969 buffer[offset] = cmdMsg->getNetCommandType();
970 offset += sizeof(UnsignedByte);
971
972 buffer[offset] = 'P';
973 ++offset;
974 buffer[offset] = cmdMsg->getPlayerID();
975 offset += sizeof(UnsignedByte);
976
977 // Put in the command id of the command we are acking.
978 buffer[offset] = 'D';
979 ++offset;
980 memcpy(buffer + offset, &commandID, sizeof(UnsignedShort));
981 offset += sizeof(UnsignedShort);
982 memcpy(buffer + offset, &originalPlayerID, sizeof(UnsignedByte));
983 offset += sizeof(UnsignedByte);
984
985 // DEBUG_LOG(("outgoing - added ACK, original player %d, command id %d\n", origPlayerID, cmdID));
986}

1644void NetPacket::FillBufferWithFileMessage(UnsignedByte *buffer, NetCommandRef *msg) {
1645 NetFileCommandMsg *cmdMsg = (NetFileCommandMsg *)(msg->getCommand());
1646 UnsignedInt offset = 0;
1647
1648 // command type
1649 buffer[offset] = 'T';
1650 ++offset;
1651 buffer[offset] = cmdMsg->getNetCommandType();
1652 offset += sizeof(UnsignedByte);
1653
1654 // relay
1655 buffer[offset] = 'R';
1656 ++offset;
1657 buffer[offset] = msg->getRelay();
1658 offset += sizeof(UnsignedByte);
1659
1660 // player ID
1661 buffer[offset] = 'P';
1662 ++offset;
1663 buffer[offset] = cmdMsg->getPlayerID();
1664 offset += sizeof(UnsignedByte);
1665
1666 // command ID
1667 buffer[offset] = 'C';
1668 ++offset;
1669 UnsignedShort newID = cmdMsg->getID();
1670 memcpy(buffer + offset, &newID, sizeof(newID));
1671 offset += sizeof(newID);
1672
1673 // data
1674 buffer[offset] = 'D';
1675 ++offset;
1676
1677 AsciiString filename = cmdMsg->getPortableFilename(); // PORTABLE
1678 for (Int i = 0; i < filename.getLength(); ++i) {
1679 buffer[offset] = filename.getCharAt(i);
1680 ++offset;
1681 }
1682 buffer[offset] = 0;
1683 ++offset;
1684
1685 UnsignedInt newInt = cmdMsg->getFileLength();
1686 memcpy(buffer + offset, &newInt, sizeof(newInt));
1687 offset += sizeof(newInt);
1688
1689 memcpy(buffer + offset, cmdMsg->getFileData(), cmdMsg->getFileLength());
1690 offset += cmdMsg->getFileLength();
1691}

1963
1968Bool NetPacket::addCommand(NetCommandRef *msg) {
1969 // This is where the fun begins...
1970
1971 NetCommandMsg *cmdMsg = msg->getCommand();
1972
1973 if (msg == NULL) {
1974 return TRUE; // There was nothing to add, so it was successful.
1975 }
1976
1977 switch(cmdMsg->getNetCommandType())
1978 {
1979 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_GAMECOMMAND:
1980 return addGameCommand(msg);
1981 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_ACKSTAGE1:
1982 return addAckStage1Command(msg);
1983 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_ACKSTAGE2:
1984 return addAckStage2Command(msg);
1985 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_ACKBOTH:
1986 return addAckBothCommand(msg);
1987 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_FRAMEINFO:
1988 return addFrameCommand(msg);
1989 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_PLAYERLEAVE:
1990 return addPlayerLeaveCommand(msg);
1991 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_RUNAHEADMETRICS:
1992 return addRunAheadMetricsCommand(msg);
1993 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_RUNAHEAD:
1994 return addRunAheadCommand(msg);
1995 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_DESTROYPLAYER:
1996 return addDestroyPlayerCommand(msg);
1997 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_KEEPALIVE:
1998 return addKeepAliveCommand(msg);
1999 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_DISCONNECTKEEPALIVE:
2000 return addDisconnectKeepAliveCommand(msg);
2001 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_DISCONNECTPLAYER:
2002 return addDisconnectPlayerCommand(msg);
2003 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_PACKETROUTERQUERY:
2004 return addPacketRouterQueryCommand(msg);

2044P = Player ID
2045C = Command ID
2046R = Relay
2047D = Command Data
2048Z = Repeat last command
2049*/
2050Bool NetPacket::addFrameResendRequestCommand(NetCommandRef *msg) {
2051 Bool needNewCommandID = FALSE;
2052 if (isRoomForFrameResendRequestMessage(msg)) {
2053 NetFrameResendRequestCommandMsg *cmdMsg = (NetFrameResendRequestCommandMsg *)(msg->getCommand());
2054
2055 // If necessary, put the NetCommandType into the packet.
2056 if (m_lastCommandType != cmdMsg->getNetCommandType()) {
2057 m_packet[m_packetLen] = 'T';
2058 ++m_packetLen;
2059 m_packet[m_packetLen] = cmdMsg->getNetCommandType();
2060 m_packetLen += sizeof(UnsignedByte);
2061
2062 m_lastCommandType = cmdMsg->getNetCommandType();
2063 }
2064
2065 // If necessary, put the execution frame into the packet.
2066 if (m_lastFrame != cmdMsg->getExecutionFrame()) {
2067 m_packet[m_packetLen] = 'F';
2068 ++m_packetLen;
2069 UnsignedInt newframe = cmdMsg->getExecutionFrame();
2070 memcpy(m_packet+m_packetLen, &newframe, sizeof(UnsignedInt));
2071 m_packetLen += sizeof(UnsignedInt);
2072
2073 m_lastFrame = newframe;
2074 }
2075
2076 // If necessary, put the relay into the packet.
2077 if (m_lastRelay != msg->getRelay()) {
2078 m_packet[m_packetLen] = 'R';
2079 ++m_packetLen;
2080 UnsignedByte newRelay = msg->getRelay();
2081 memcpy(m_packet + m_packetLen, &newRelay, sizeof(UnsignedByte));
2082 m_packetLen += sizeof(UnsignedByte);
2083
2084 m_lastRelay = newRelay;
2085 }
2086
2087 // If necessary put the player ID into the packet.
2088 if (m_lastPlayerID != cmdMsg->getPlayerID()) {
2089 m_packet[m_packetLen] = 'P';

2091 m_packet[m_packetLen] = cmdMsg->getPlayerID();
2092 m_packetLen += sizeof(UnsignedByte);
2093
2094 m_lastPlayerID = cmdMsg->getPlayerID();
2095 needNewCommandID = TRUE;
2096 }
2097
2098 // If necessary, specify the command ID of this command.
2099 if (((m_lastCommandID + 1) != (UnsignedShort)(cmdMsg->getID())) || (needNewCommandID == TRUE)) {
2100 m_packet[m_packetLen] = 'C';
2101 ++m_packetLen;
2102 UnsignedShort newID = cmdMsg->getID();
2103 memcpy(m_packet + m_packetLen, &newID, sizeof(UnsignedShort));
2104 m_packetLen += sizeof(UnsignedShort);
2105 }
2106 m_lastCommandID = cmdMsg->getID();
2107
2108 m_packet[m_packetLen] = 'D';
2109 ++m_packetLen;
2110
2111 UnsignedInt frameToResend = cmdMsg->getFrameToResend();
2112 memcpy(m_packet + m_packetLen, &frameToResend, sizeof(frameToResend));
2113 m_packetLen += sizeof(frameToResend);
2114
2115 DEBUG_LOG(("NetPacket::addFrameResendRequest - added frame resend request command from player %d for frame %d, command id = %d\n", m_lastPlayerID, frameToResend, m_lastCommandID));
2116
2117 ++m_numCommands;
2118 if (m_lastCommand != NULL) {
2119 m_lastCommand->deleteInstance();
2120 m_lastCommand = NULL;
2121 }
2122 m_lastCommand = NEW_NETCOMMANDREF(msg->getCommand());
2123 m_lastCommand->setRelay(msg->getRelay());
2124
2125 return TRUE;
2126 }
2127 return FALSE;

4494Bool NetPacket::isFrameRepeat(NetCommandRef *msg) {
4495 if (m_lastCommand == NULL) {
4496 return FALSE;
4497 }
4498 if (m_lastCommand->getCommand()->getNetCommandType() != NETCOMMANDTYPE_FRAMEINFO) {
4499 return FALSE;
4500 }
4501 NetFrameCommandMsg *framemsg = (NetFrameCommandMsg *)(msg->getCommand());
4502 NetFrameCommandMsg *lastmsg = (NetFrameCommandMsg *)(m_lastCommand->getCommand());
4503 if (framemsg->getCommandCount() != 0) {
4504 return FALSE;
4505 }
4506 if (framemsg->getExecutionFrame() != (lastmsg->getExecutionFrame() + 1)) {
4507 return FALSE;
4508 }
4509 if (msg->getRelay() != m_lastCommand->getRelay()) {
4510 return FALSE;
4511 }
4512 if (framemsg->getID() != (lastmsg->getID() + 1)) {
4513 return FALSE;
4514 }
4515 return TRUE;

4560 if (isRoomForAckMessage(msg)) {
4561 NetCommandMsg *cmdMsg = msg->getCommand();
4562// DEBUG_LOG(("NetPacket::addAckCommand - adding ack for command %d for player %d\n", cmdMsg->getCommandID(), msg->getCommand()->getPlayerID()));
4563 // If necessary, put the NetCommandType into the packet.
4564 if (m_lastCommandType != cmdMsg->getNetCommandType()) {
4565 m_packet[m_packetLen] = 'T';
4566 ++m_packetLen;
4567 m_packet[m_packetLen] = cmdMsg->getNetCommandType();
4568 m_packetLen += sizeof(UnsignedByte);
4569
4570 m_lastCommandType = cmdMsg->getNetCommandType();
4571 }
4572
4573 if (m_lastPlayerID != cmdMsg->getPlayerID()) {
4574 m_packet[m_packetLen] = 'P';
4575 ++m_packetLen;
4576 m_packet[m_packetLen] = cmdMsg->getPlayerID();
4577 m_packetLen += sizeof(UnsignedByte);
4578
4579 m_lastPlayerID = cmdMsg->getPlayerID();
4580 }
4581
4582 // Put in the command id of the command we are acking.
4583 m_packet[m_packetLen] = 'D';
4584 ++m_packetLen;
4585 memcpy(m_packet + m_packetLen, &commandID, sizeof(UnsignedShort));
4586 m_packetLen += sizeof(UnsignedShort);
4587 memcpy(m_packet + m_packetLen, &originalPlayerID, sizeof(UnsignedByte));
4588 m_packetLen += sizeof(UnsignedByte);
4589
4590 if (m_lastCommand != NULL) {
4591 m_lastCommand->deleteInstance();
4592 m_lastCommand = NULL;
4593 }
4594 m_lastCommand = NEW_NETCOMMANDREF(msg->getCommand());
4595 m_lastCommand->setRelay(msg->getRelay());
4596
4597// DEBUG_LOG(("outgoing - added ACK, original player %d, command id %d\n", origPlayerID, cmdID));
4598 ++m_numCommands;
4599 return TRUE;
4600 }
4601 return FALSE;
4602}

4607Bool NetPacket::isRoomForAckMessage(NetCommandRef *msg) {
4608 Int len = 0;
4609 NetCommandMsg *cmdMsg = msg->getCommand();
4610 if (m_lastCommandType != cmdMsg->getNetCommandType()) {
4611 ++len;
4612 len += sizeof(UnsignedByte);
4613 }
4614 if (m_lastPlayerID != cmdMsg->getPlayerID()) {
4615 ++len;
4616 len += sizeof(UnsignedByte);
4617 }
4618
4619 ++len; // for 'D'
4620 len += sizeof(UnsignedShort);
4621 len += sizeof(UnsignedByte);
4622 if ((len + m_packetLen) > MAX_PACKET_SIZE) {
4623 return FALSE;
4624 }
4625 return TRUE;

4630 return FALSE;
4631 }

4640 }
4641 if (msg->getCommand()->getNetCommandType() == NETCOMMANDTYPE_ACKSTAGE2) {
4642 return isAckStage2Repeat(msg);
4643 }
4644 return FALSE;

4695Bool NetPacket::addGameCommand(NetCommandRef *msg) {
4696 Bool retval = FALSE;
4697 NetGameCommandMsg *cmdMsg = (NetGameCommandMsg *)(msg->getCommand());
4698 // get the game message from the NetCommandMsg
4699 GameMessage *gmsg = cmdMsg->constructGameMessage();
4700
4701// DEBUG_LOG(("NetPacket::addGameCommand for command ID %d\n", cmdMsg->getID()));
4702
4703 if (isRoomForGameMessage(msg, gmsg)) {
4704 // Now we know there is enough room, put the new game message into the packet.
4705
4706 Bool needNewCommandID = FALSE; // this is to allow us to force the starting command ID to be respecified with this command.
4707
4708 // If necessary, put the NetCommandType into the packet.
4709 if (m_lastCommandType != cmdMsg->getNetCommandType()) {
4710 m_packet[m_packetLen] = 'T';
4711 ++m_packetLen;
4712 m_packet[m_packetLen] = cmdMsg->getNetCommandType();
4713 m_packetLen += sizeof(UnsignedByte);
4714
4715 m_lastCommandType = cmdMsg->getNetCommandType();
4716 }
4717
4718 // If necessary, put the execution frame into the packet.
4719 if (m_lastFrame != cmdMsg->getExecutionFrame()) {
4720 m_packet[m_packetLen] = 'F';
4721 ++m_packetLen;
4722 UnsignedInt newframe = cmdMsg->getExecutionFrame();
4723 memcpy(m_packet+m_packetLen, &newframe, sizeof(UnsignedInt));
4724 m_packetLen += sizeof(UnsignedInt);
4725
4726 m_lastFrame = newframe;
4727 }
4728
4729 // If necessary, put the relay into the packet.
4730 if (m_lastRelay != msg->getRelay()) {
4731 m_packet[m_packetLen] = 'R';
4732 ++m_packetLen;
4733 UnsignedByte newRelay = msg->getRelay();
4734 memcpy(m_packet+m_packetLen, &newRelay, sizeof(UnsignedByte));
4735 m_packetLen += sizeof(UnsignedByte);
4736
4737 m_lastRelay = newRelay;
4738 }
4739
4740 // If necessary, put the playerID into the packet.
4741 if (m_lastPlayerID != cmdMsg->getPlayerID()) {
4742 m_packet[m_packetLen] = 'P';
4743 ++m_packetLen;
4744 m_packet[m_packetLen] = cmdMsg->getPlayerID();
4745 m_packetLen += sizeof(UnsignedByte);
4746 //since if we have a new player we need to respecify the starting command ID, lets force the command id to be different.
4747 needNewCommandID = TRUE;
4748
4749 m_lastPlayerID = cmdMsg->getPlayerID();
4750 }
4751
4752 // If necessary, specify the command ID of this command.
4753 if (((m_lastCommandID + 1) != (UnsignedShort)(cmdMsg->getID())) || (needNewCommandID == TRUE)) {
4754 m_packet[m_packetLen] = 'C';
4755 ++m_packetLen;
4756 UnsignedShort newID = cmdMsg->getID();
4757 memcpy(m_packet + m_packetLen, &newID, sizeof(UnsignedShort));
4758 m_packetLen += sizeof(UnsignedShort);
4759 }
4760 m_lastCommandID = cmdMsg->getID();
4761
4762 m_packet[m_packetLen] = 'D';
4763 ++m_packetLen;
4764
4765 // Now copy the GameMessage type into the packet.
4766 GameMessage::Type newType = gmsg->getType();
4767 memcpy(m_packet + m_packetLen, &newType, sizeof(GameMessage::Type));
4768 m_packetLen += sizeof(GameMessage::Type);
4769
4770
4771 GameMessageParser *parser = newInstance(GameMessageParser)(gmsg);
4772 UnsignedByte numTypes = parser->getNumTypes();
4773 memcpy(m_packet + m_packetLen, &numTypes, sizeof(numTypes));
4774 m_packetLen += sizeof(numTypes);
4775
4776 GameMessageParserArgumentType *argType = parser->getFirstArgumentType();
4777 while (argType != NULL) {
4778 UnsignedByte type = (UnsignedByte)(argType->getType());
4779 memcpy(m_packet + m_packetLen, &type, sizeof(type));
4780 m_packetLen += sizeof(type);
4781
4782 UnsignedByte argTypeCount = argType->getArgCount();
4783 memcpy(m_packet + m_packetLen, &argTypeCount, sizeof(argTypeCount));
4784 m_packetLen += sizeof(argTypeCount);
4785
4786 argType = argType->getNext();
4787 }
4788
4789 Int numArgs = gmsg->getArgumentCount();
4790 for (Int i = 0; i < numArgs; ++i) {
4791 GameMessageArgumentDataType type = gmsg->getArgumentDataType(i);
4792 GameMessageArgumentType arg = *(gmsg->getArgument(i));
4793 writeGameMessageArgumentToPacket(type, arg);
4794 }
4795
4796 parser->deleteInstance();
4797 parser = NULL;
4798
4799// DEBUG_LOG(("NetPacket::addGameMessage - added game message, frame %d, player %d, command ID %d\n", m_lastFrame, m_lastPlayerID, m_lastCommandID));
4800
4801 ++m_numCommands;
4802
4803 if (m_lastCommand != NULL) {
4804 m_lastCommand->deleteInstance();
4805 m_lastCommand = NULL;
4806 }
4807 m_lastCommand = NEW_NETCOMMANDREF(msg->getCommand());
4808 m_lastCommand->setRelay(msg->getRelay());
4809
4810 retval = TRUE;
4811 }
4812
4813 if (gmsg) {
4814 gmsg->deleteInstance();
4815 gmsg = NULL;
4816 }
4817
4818 return retval;
4819}

4861Bool NetPacket::isRoomForGameMessage(NetCommandRef *msg, GameMessage *gmsg) {
4862 // Calculate how much space the NetCommandMsg will take in this packet.
4863 Int msglen = 0;
4864
4865 NetGameCommandMsg *cmdMsg = (NetGameCommandMsg *)(msg->getCommand());
4866
4867 Bool needNewCommandID = FALSE;
4868
4869 if (m_lastFrame != cmdMsg->getExecutionFrame()) {
4870 msglen += sizeof(UnsignedInt) + sizeof(UnsignedByte);
4871 }
4872 if (m_lastPlayerID != cmdMsg->getPlayerID()) {
4873 msglen += sizeof(UnsignedByte) + sizeof(UnsignedByte);
4874 needNewCommandID = TRUE;
4875 }
4876 if (m_lastRelay != msg->getRelay()) {
4877 msglen += sizeof(UnsignedByte) + sizeof(UnsignedByte);
4878 }
4879 if (m_lastCommandType != cmdMsg->getNetCommandType()) {
4880 msglen += sizeof(UnsignedByte) + sizeof(UnsignedByte);
4881 }
4882 if (((m_lastCommandID + 1) != (UnsignedShort)(cmdMsg->getID())) || (needNewCommandID == TRUE)) {
4883 msglen += sizeof(UnsignedShort) + sizeof(UnsignedByte);
4884 }
4885
4886 GameMessageParser *parser = newInstance(GameMessageParser)(gmsg);
4887
4888 ++msglen; // for 'D'
4889 msglen += sizeof(GameMessage::Type);
4890 msglen += sizeof(UnsignedByte);
4891// Int numTypes = parser->getNumTypes();
4892 GameMessageParserArgumentType *arg = parser->getFirstArgumentType();
4893 while (arg != NULL) {
4894 msglen += 2 * sizeof(UnsignedByte); // for the type and number of args of that type declaration.
4895 GameMessageArgumentDataType type = arg->getType();
4896 if (type == ARGUMENTDATATYPE_INTEGER) {
4897 msglen += arg->getArgCount() * sizeof(Int);
4898 } else if (type == ARGUMENTDATATYPE_REAL) {
4899 msglen += arg->getArgCount() * sizeof(Real);
4900 } else if (type == ARGUMENTDATATYPE_BOOLEAN) {
4901 msglen += arg->getArgCount() * sizeof(Bool);
4902 } else if (type == ARGUMENTDATATYPE_OBJECTID) {
4903 msglen += arg->getArgCount() * sizeof(ObjectID);
4904 } else if (type == ARGUMENTDATATYPE_DRAWABLEID) {
4905 msglen += arg->getArgCount() * sizeof(DrawableID);
4906 } else if (type == ARGUMENTDATATYPE_TEAMID) {
4907 msglen += arg->getArgCount() * sizeof(UnsignedInt);
4908 } else if (type == ARGUMENTDATATYPE_LOCATION) {
4909 msglen += arg->getArgCount() * sizeof(Coord3D);
4910 } else if (type == ARGUMENTDATATYPE_PIXEL) {
4911 msglen += arg->getArgCount() * sizeof(ICoord2D);
4912 } else if (type == ARGUMENTDATATYPE_PIXELREGION) {
4913 msglen += arg->getArgCount() * sizeof(IRegion2D);
4914 } else if (type == ARGUMENTDATATYPE_TIMESTAMP) {
4915 msglen += arg->getArgCount() * sizeof(UnsignedInt);
4916 } else if (type == ARGUMENTDATATYPE_WIDECHAR) {
4917 msglen += arg->getArgCount() * sizeof(WideChar);
4918 }
4919 arg = arg->getNext();
4920 }
4921
4922 parser->deleteInstance();
4923 parser = NULL;
4924
4925 // Is there enough room in the packet for this message?
4926 if (msglen > (MAX_PACKET_SIZE - m_packetLen)) {
4927 return FALSE; // there isn't enough room in this packet for this new message.
4928 }
4929 return TRUE;
4930}

4935NetCommandList * NetPacket::getCommandList() {
4936 NetCommandList *retval = newInstance(NetCommandList);
4937// DEBUG_LOG(("NetPacket::getCommandList, packet length = %d\n", m_packetLen));
4938 retval->init();
4939
4940 // These need to be the same as the default values for m_lastPlayerID, m_lastFrame, etc.
4941 UnsignedByte playerID = 0;
4942 UnsignedInt frame = 0;
4943 UnsignedShort commandID = 1; // The first command is going to be
4944 UnsignedByte commandType = 0;
4945 UnsignedByte relay = 0;
4946 NetCommandRef *lastCommand = NULL;
4947
4948 Int i = 0;
4949 while (i < m_packetLen) {
4950 if (m_packet[i] == 'T') {
4951 ++i;
4952 memcpy(&commandType, m_packet + i, sizeof(UnsignedByte));
4953 i += sizeof(UnsignedByte);
4954 } else if (m_packet[i] == 'F') {
4955 ++i;
4956 memcpy(&frame, m_packet + i, sizeof(UnsignedInt));
4957 i += sizeof(UnsignedInt);
4958 } else if (m_packet[i] == 'P') {
4959 ++i;
4960 memcpy(&playerID, m_packet + i, sizeof(UnsignedByte));
4961 i += sizeof(UnsignedByte);
4962 } else if (m_packet[i] == 'R') {
4963 ++i;
4964 memcpy(&relay, m_packet + i, sizeof(UnsignedByte));
4965 i += sizeof(UnsignedByte);
4966 } else if (m_packet[i] == 'C') {
4967 ++i;
4968 memcpy(&commandID, m_packet + i, sizeof(UnsignedShort));
4969 i += sizeof(UnsignedShort);
4970 } else if (m_packet[i] == 'D') {
4971 ++i;
4972
4973 NetCommandMsg *msg = NULL;
4974
4975 //DEBUG_LOG(("NetPacket::getCommandList() - command of type %d(%s)\n", commandType, GetAsciiNetCommandType((NetCommandType)commandType).str()));
4976
4977 switch((NetCommandType)commandType)
4978 {
4979 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_GAMECOMMAND:
4980 msg = readGameMessage(m_packet, i);
4981 //DEBUG_LOG(("read game command from player %d for frame %d\n", playerID, frame));
4982 break;
4983 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_ACKBOTH:
4984 msg = readAckBothMessage(m_packet, i);
4985 break;
4986 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_ACKSTAGE1:
4987 msg = readAckStage1Message(m_packet, i);
4988 break;
4989 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_ACKSTAGE2:
4990 msg = readAckStage2Message(m_packet, i);
4991 break;
4992 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_FRAMEINFO:
4993 msg = readFrameMessage(m_packet, i);
4994 // frameinfodebug
4995 DEBUG_LOG(("read frame %d from player %d, command count = %d, relay = 0x%X\n", frame, playerID, ((NetFrameCommandMsg *)msg)->getCommandCount(), relay));
4996 break;
4997 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_PLAYERLEAVE:
4998 msg = readPlayerLeaveMessage(m_packet, i);
4999// DEBUG_LOG(("read player leave message from player %d for execution on frame %d\n", playerID, frame));
5000 break;
5001 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_RUNAHEADMETRICS:
5002 msg = readRunAheadMetricsMessage(m_packet, i);
5003 break;
5004 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_RUNAHEAD:
5005 msg = readRunAheadMessage(m_packet, i);
5006// DEBUG_LOG(("read run ahead message from player %d for execution on frame %d\n", playerID, frame));
5007 break;
5008 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_DESTROYPLAYER:
5009 msg = readDestroyPlayerMessage(m_packet, i);
5010// DEBUG_LOG(("read CRC info message from player %d for execution on frame %d\n", playerID, frame));
5011 break;
5012 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_KEEPALIVE:
5013 msg = readKeepAliveMessage(m_packet, i);
5014// DEBUG_LOG(("read keep alive message from player %d\n", playerID));
5015 break;
5016 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_DISCONNECTKEEPALIVE:
5017 msg = readDisconnectKeepAliveMessage(m_packet, i);
5018// DEBUG_LOG(("read keep alive message from player %d\n", playerID));
5019 break;
5020 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_DISCONNECTPLAYER:
5021 msg = readDisconnectPlayerMessage(m_packet, i);
5022// DEBUG_LOG(("read disconnect player message from player %d\n", playerID));
5023 break;
5024 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_PACKETROUTERQUERY:
5025 msg = readPacketRouterQueryMessage(m_packet, i);
5026// DEBUG_LOG(("read packet router query message from player %d\n", playerID));
5027 break;
5028 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_PACKETROUTERACK:
5029 msg = readPacketRouterAckMessage(m_packet, i);
5030// DEBUG_LOG(("read packet router ack message from player %d\n", playerID));
5031 break;
5032 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_DISCONNECTCHAT:
5033 msg = readDisconnectChatMessage(m_packet, i);
5034// DEBUG_LOG(("read disconnect chat message from player %d\n", playerID));
5035 break;
5036 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_DISCONNECTVOTE:
5037 msg = readDisconnectVoteMessage(m_packet, i);
5038// DEBUG_LOG(("read disconnect vote message from player %d\n", playerID));
5039 break;
5040 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_CHAT:
5041 msg = readChatMessage(m_packet, i);
5042// DEBUG_LOG(("read chat message from player %d\n", playerID));
5043 break;
5044 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_PROGRESS:
5045 msg = readProgressMessage(m_packet, i);
5046// DEBUG_LOG(("read Progress message from player %d\n", playerID));
5047 break;
5048 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_LOADCOMPLETE:
5049 msg = readLoadCompleteMessage(m_packet, i);
5050// DEBUG_LOG(("read LoadComplete message from player %d\n", playerID));
5051 break;
5052 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_TIMEOUTSTART:
5053 msg = readTimeOutGameStartMessage(m_packet, i);
5054// DEBUG_LOG(("read TimeOutGameStart message from player %d\n", playerID));
5055 break;
5056 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_WRAPPER:
5057 DEBUG_LOG(("read Wrapper message from player %d\n", playerID));
5058 msg = readWrapperMessage(m_packet, i);
5059 DEBUG_LOG(("Done reading Wrapper message from player %d - wrapped command was %d\n", playerID,
5060 ((NetWrapperCommandMsg *)msg)->getWrappedCommandID()));
5061 break;
5062 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_FILE:
5063 DEBUG_LOG(("read file message from player %d\n", playerID));
5064 msg = readFileMessage(m_packet, i);
5065 break;
5066 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_FILEANNOUNCE:
5067 DEBUG_LOG(("read file announce message from player %d\n", playerID));
5068 msg = readFileAnnounceMessage(m_packet, i);
5069 break;
5070 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_FILEPROGRESS:
5071 DEBUG_LOG(("read file progress message from player %d\n", playerID));
5072 msg = readFileProgressMessage(m_packet, i);
5073 break;
5074 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_DISCONNECTFRAME:
5075 DEBUG_LOG(("read disconnect frame message from player %d\n", playerID));
5076 msg = readDisconnectFrameMessage(m_packet, i);
5077 break;
5078 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_DISCONNECTSCREENOFF:
5079 DEBUG_LOG(("read disconnect screen off message from player %d\n", playerID));
5080 msg = readDisconnectScreenOffMessage(m_packet, i);
5081 break;
5082 case NETCOMMANDTYPE_FRAMERESENDREQUEST:
5083 DEBUG_LOG(("read frame resend request message from player %d\n", playerID));
5084 msg = readFrameResendRequestMessage(m_packet, i);
5085 break;
5086 }
5087
5088 if (msg == NULL) {
5089 DEBUG_CRASH(("Didn't read a message from the packet. Things are about to go wrong."));
5090 continue;
5091 }
5092
5093 // set the info
5094 msg->setExecutionFrame(frame);
5095 msg->setPlayerID(playerID);
5096 msg->setNetCommandType((NetCommandType)commandType);
5097 msg->setID(commandID);
5098
5099// DEBUG_LOG(("frame = %d, player = %d, command type = %d, id = %d\n", frame, playerID, commandType, commandID));
5100
5101 // increment to the next command ID.
5102 if (DoesCommandRequireACommandID((NetCommandType)commandType)) {
5103 ++commandID;
5104 }
5105
5106 // add the message to the list.
5107 NetCommandRef *ref = retval->addMessage(msg);
5108 if (ref != NULL) {
5109 ref->setRelay(relay);
5110 } else {
5111 DEBUG_LOG(("NetPacket::getCommandList - failed to set relay for message %d\n", msg->getID()));
5112 }
5113
5114 if (lastCommand != NULL) {
5115 lastCommand->deleteInstance();
5116 lastCommand = NULL;
5117 }
5118 lastCommand = newInstance(NetCommandRef)(msg);
5119
5120 msg->detach(); // Need to detach from new NetCommandMsg created by the "readXMessage" above.
5121
5122 // since the message is part of the list now, we don't have to keep track of it. So we'll just set it to NULL.
5123 msg = NULL;
5124 } else if (m_packet[i] == 'Z') {
5125 ++i;
5126 // Repeat the last command, doing some funky cool byte-saving stuff
5127 if (lastCommand == NULL) {
5128 DEBUG_CRASH(("Got a repeat command with no command to repeat."));
5129 }
5130 NetCommandMsg *msg = NULL;
5131 if (commandType == NETCOMMANDTYPE_ACKSTAGE1) {
5132 msg = newInstance(NetAckStage1CommandMsg)();
5133 NetAckStage1CommandMsg *last = (NetAckStage1CommandMsg *)(lastCommand->getCommand());
5134 ((NetAckStage1CommandMsg *)msg)->setCommandID(last->getCommandID() + 1);
5135 ((NetAckStage1CommandMsg *)msg)->setOriginalPlayerID(last->getOriginalPlayerID());
5136 } else if (commandType == NETCOMMANDTYPE_ACKSTAGE2) {
5137 msg = newInstance(NetAckStage2CommandMsg)();
5138 NetAckStage2CommandMsg *last = (NetAckStage2CommandMsg *)(lastCommand->getCommand());
5139 ((NetAckStage2CommandMsg *)msg)->setCommandID(last->getCommandID() + 1);
5140 ((NetAckStage2CommandMsg *)msg)->setOriginalPlayerID(last->getOriginalPlayerID());
5141 } else if (commandType == NETCOMMANDTYPE_ACKBOTH) {
5142 msg = newInstance(NetAckBothCommandMsg)();
5143 NetAckBothCommandMsg *last = (NetAckBothCommandMsg *)(lastCommand->getCommand());
5144 ((NetAckBothCommandMsg *)msg)->setCommandID(last->getCommandID() + 1);
5145 ((NetAckBothCommandMsg *)msg)->setOriginalPlayerID(last->getOriginalPlayerID());
5146 } else if (commandType == NETCOMMANDTYPE_FRAMEINFO) {
5147 msg = newInstance(NetFrameCommandMsg)();
5148 ++frame; // this is set below.
5149 ((NetFrameCommandMsg *)msg)->setCommandCount(0);
5150 DEBUG_LOG(("Read a repeated frame command, frame = %d, player = %d, commandID = %d\n", frame, playerID, commandID));
5151 } else {
5152 DEBUG_CRASH(("Trying to repeat a command that shouldn't be repeated."));
5153 continue;
5154 }
5155
5156 msg->setExecutionFrame(frame);
5157 msg->setPlayerID(playerID);
5158 msg->setNetCommandType((NetCommandType)commandType);
5159 msg->setID(commandID);
5160
5161// DEBUG_LOG(("frame = %d, player = %d, command type = %d, id = %d\n", frame, playerID, commandType, commandID));
5162
5163 // increment to the next command ID.
5164 if (DoesCommandRequireACommandID((NetCommandType)commandType)) {
5165 ++commandID;
5166 }
5167
5168 // add the message to the list.
5169 NetCommandRef *ref = retval->addMessage(msg);
5170 if (ref != NULL) {
5171 ref->setRelay(relay);
5172 }
5173
5174 lastCommand->deleteInstance();
5175 lastCommand = NULL;
5176// lastCommand = newInstance(NetCommandRef)(msg);
5177 lastCommand = NEW_NETCOMMANDREF(msg);
5178
5179 msg->detach(); // Need to detach from new NetCommandMsg created by the "readXMessage" above.
5180
5181 // since the message is part of the list now, we don't have to keep track of it. So we'll just set it to NULL.
5182 msg = NULL;
5183 } else {
5184 // we don't recognize this command, but we have to increment i so we don't fall into an infinite loop.
5185 DEBUG_CRASH(("Unrecognized packet entry, ignoring."));
5186 DEBUG_LOG(("NetPacket::getCommandList - Unrecognized packet entry at index %d\n", i));
5187 dumpPacketToLog();
5188 ++i;
5189 }
5190 }
5191
5192 if (lastCommand != NULL) {
5193 lastCommand->deleteInstance();
5194 lastCommand = NULL;
5195 }
5196 return retval;
5197}
5198
5202NetCommandMsg * NetPacket::readGameMessage(UnsignedByte *data, Int &i)
5203{
5204 NetGameCommandMsg *msg = newInstance(NetGameCommandMsg);
5205
5206// DEBUG_LOG(("NetPacket::readGameMessage\n"));
5207
5208 // Get the GameMessage command type.
5209 GameMessage::Type newType;
5210 memcpy(&newType, data + i, sizeof(GameMessage::Type));
5211 i += sizeof(GameMessage::Type);
5212 msg->setGameMessageType(newType);
5213
5214 // Get the number of argument types
5215 UnsignedByte numArgTypes = 0;
5216 memcpy(&numArgTypes, data + i, sizeof(numArgTypes));
5217 i += sizeof(numArgTypes);
5218
5219 // Get the types and the number of arguments of those types.
5220 Int totalArgCount = 0;
5221 GameMessageParser *parser = newInstance(GameMessageParser)();
5222 for (Int j = 0; j < numArgTypes; ++j) {
5223 UnsignedByte type = (UnsignedByte)ARGUMENTDATATYPE_UNKNOWN;
5224 memcpy(&type, data + i, sizeof(type));
5225 i += sizeof(type);
5226
5227 UnsignedByte argCount = 0;
5228 memcpy(&argCount, data + i, sizeof(argCount));
5229 i += sizeof(argCount);
5230
5231 parser->addArgType((GameMessageArgumentDataType)type, argCount);
5232 totalArgCount += argCount;
5233 }
5234
5235 GameMessageParserArgumentType *parserArgType = parser->getFirstArgumentType();
5236 GameMessageArgumentDataType lasttype = ARGUMENTDATATYPE_UNKNOWN;
5237 Int argsLeftForType = 0;
5238 if (parserArgType != NULL) {
5239 lasttype = parserArgType->getType();
5240 argsLeftForType = parserArgType->getArgCount();
5241 }
5242 for (j = 0; j < totalArgCount; ++j) {
5243 readGameMessageArgumentFromPacket(lasttype, msg, data, i);
5244
5245 --argsLeftForType;
5246 if (argsLeftForType == 0) {
5247 DEBUG_ASSERTCRASH(parserArgType != NULL, ("parserArgType was NULL when it shouldn't have been."));
5248 if (parserArgType == NULL) {
5249 return NULL;
5250 }
5251
5252 parserArgType = parserArgType->getNext();
5253 // parserArgType is allowed to be NULL here
5254 if (parserArgType != NULL) {
5255 argsLeftForType = parserArgType->getArgCount();
5256 lasttype = parserArgType->getType();
5257 }
5258 }
5259 }
5260
5261 parser->deleteInstance();
5262 parser = NULL;
5263
5264 return (NetCommandMsg *)msg;
5265}

5701 NetFileCommandMsg *msg = newInstance(NetFileCommandMsg);

5703 char *c = filename;
5704
5705 while (data[i] != 0) {

5707 ++c;
5708 ++i;

5710 *c = 0;
5711 ++i;
5712 msg->setPortableFilename(AsciiString(filename)); // it's transferred as a portable filename

5717

5720 i += dataLength;

5722 msg->setFileData(buf, dataLength);
5723
5724 return msg;

5843void NetPacket::dumpPacketToLog() {
5844 DEBUG_LOG(("NetPacket::dumpPacketToLog() - packet is %d bytes\n", m_packetLen));
5845 Int numLines = m_packetLen / 8;
5846 if ((m_packetLen % 8) != 0) {
5847 ++numLines;
